# FANUC TP/LS Conventions

These conventions apply when authoring or reviewing `.LS` (ASCII source) and `.TP` (binary) programs for FANUC R-30iB-family controllers running V9.x.

## Header discipline

Every `.LS` program starts with a header block containing at minimum:

```
/PROG  <PROGRAM_NAME>
/ATTR
OWNER           = MNEDITOR;
COMMENT         = "<short description>";
PROG_SIZE       = <>;
CREATE          = <date/time>;
MODIFIED        = <date/time>;
FILE_NAME       = ;
VERSION         = 0;
LINE_COUNT      = <>;
MEMORY_SIZE     = <>;
PROTECT         = READ_WRITE;
TCD:  STACK_SIZE   = 0,
      TASK_PRIORITY = 50,
      TIME_SLICE    = 0,
      BUSY_LAMP_OFF = 0,
      ABORT_REQUEST = 0,
      PAUSE_REQUEST = 0;
DEFAULT_GROUP = 1,*,*,*,*;
CONTROL_CODE  = 00000000 00000000;
```

Program name uppercase, <=36 chars, no leading digits.

## Motion instructions

- Use `J`, `L`, `C`, `A` for joint / linear / circular / arc.
- Always name the speed: `100%`, `500mm/sec`, `WELD_SPEED`.
- Termination: `FINE` for precise stops, `CNT0..CNT100` for blending. Default to `CNT100` for rapid traverse moves and `FINE` for approach/retract and work points.
- Never use `P[n]` (program-local position) for anything that might be retaught by a customer. Prefer `PR[n:COMMENT]` (position register) whenever the point is shared, taught at install, or tuned at runtime.

Examples:

```
 1:J P[1] 100% FINE    ;
 2:L P[2] 500mm/sec CNT50    ;
 3:L PR[5:PICK_APPROACH] 300mm/sec FINE    ;
```

## UTool / UFrame

Set both at the top of any motion-containing program, before the first motion line:

```
 1: UTOOL_NUM=1 ;
 2: UFRAME_NUM=2 ;
```

Never assume. Never modify them mid-program unless the program is explicitly a tool-change routine.

## I/O discipline

- Never use raw indices (`DI[123]`, `DO[45]`) in program bodies. Always use aliased names via signal Comments: `DI[123:PB_START]`, `DO[45:GRIPPER_CLOSE]`.
- If a signal lacks a comment in the controller configuration, stop and add one before coding.
- Group signals (`GI[]`, `GO[]`) carry part IDs, style codes, error codes. Document the bit-ordering in the `INTEGRATION_SPEC`.

## WAIT with timeout

Every `WAIT DI[]=ON` MUST have a `TIMEOUT,LBL[n]` branch that routes to a fault recovery:

```
 12: WAIT DI[123:PB_START]=ON TIMEOUT,LBL[99] ;
 ...
 99:LBL[99:WAIT_PB_START_TIMEOUT] ;
 100: UALM[3:PB_START_TIMEOUT] ;
```

Unbounded WAITs are a FANUC-SAFETY-LINT rule `FANUC-WAIT-001` violation.

## Skip and Condition

- `SKIP CONDITION DI[n]=ON` must be paired with a `LBL[]` receiver before any subsequent motion.
- `MONITOR <cond_prog>` must be closed with `MONITOR END <cond_prog>` in the same logical scope.

## Flow control

- Labels `LBL[n:NAME]` - always name them in the comment for readability.
- Jumps `JMP LBL[n]` - avoid into the middle of motion blocks.
- Error recovery: use `UALM[n]` to raise named alarms, not bare aborts.

## Register conventions

- `R[n:NAME]` for scalars. Typical buckets:
  - `R[1..10]`: part flags / part IDs.
  - `R[11..30]`: counters (cycle, reject, good).
  - `R[31..50]`: timers.
  - `R[51..70]`: error state / status codes.
  - `R[90..100]`: customer convention varies; confirm in customer spec before use.
- `PR[n:NAME]` for positions, with comment naming. Group-scoped when using multi-group.
- Always initialize registers explicitly; never rely on power-on defaults.

## Program kinds

- `PNS<NNNN>.LS` - selected by PNS handshake (UOP). Thin; usually calls a style-specific program.
- `PNS<NNNN>_R01.LS` - revision copy; keep under `customer_programs/<c>/backups/`.
- `MAIN.LS` / `HOME.LS` / `GO_*.LS` - utility programs, no teach positions if avoidable.
- `BG_LOGIC.LS` - Background Logic program. Must not call motion. Must not modify registers used by foreground motion programs.
- `*_HOME.LS` - always use `PR[1:HOME]`, never `P[1]`.

## Comments

Short, uppercase-first, no trailing punctuation. Align within blocks where it aids scanning.

## Anti-patterns (fail review)

- `OVERRIDE` modification from TP (`$MCR_GRP[].$PRGOVERRIDE`).
- Hardcoded `P[n]` for runtime-tuned points.
- `WAIT DI[n]=ON` without `TIMEOUT`.
- `SKIP CONDITION` without `LBL[]` receiver.
- Raw `DI[]/DO[]` in body.
- Motion before `UTOOL_NUM` / `UFRAME_NUM` set.
- Background Logic program issuing motion (`J`, `L`, `C`, `A`, `PALLETIZING_*`).
- Mixed CR (collaborative) + non-collaborative groups without DCS validation.

Canon reference: `fanuc_dataset/normalized/reference/FANUC_REF_TP_*`. Cite by ID.
